ng star forming to passive.\nComparing the fraction of PSBs to the fraction of galaxies in transition on\nlonger timescales, we estimate that the short timescale star-formation\nquenching channel contributes two times more than the long timescale one to the\ngrowth of the passive population. Processes like ram-pressure stripping and\ngalaxy-galaxy interactions are more efficient than strangulation in affecting\nstar formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Mar 2017 09:55:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-12"}
