{"id":"1703.03240","submitter":"Kirk Sturtz","authors":"Kirk Sturtz","title":"The equivalence between the categories of Giry-algebras and convex\n  spaces","comments":"31 pages. The update uses the fact that the full subcategory\n  consisting of just the unit interval is both a dense and codense subcategory,\n  which simplifies several arguments","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CT math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A duality between the category of convex spaces and measurable spaces arises\nfrom the existence of the unit interval, which is an object in both these\ncategories. The full subcategory of the category of convex spaces, consisting\nof just the single object, the unit interval, is both a dense and codense\nsubcategory in the category of convex spaces. Combined with the the symmetric\nmonoidal closed category structure of the category, one obtains the double\ndualization monad into the unit interval, which sends a point to the evaluation\nmap at that point. The restriction of the codomain of the unit of this monad to\nthe weakly averaging affine functionals is an isomorphism. Moreover, every\nconvex space has an associated measurable space, whose {\\sigma}-algebra is\ngenerated by the Boolean subobjects of that convex space. The resulting\n{\\sigma}- algebra of that measurable space makes it a separated measurable\nspace. These properties are used to give a proof that the category of Giry\nalgebras is equivalent to the category of convex spaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Mar 2017 12:05:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 Mar 2017 09:54:05 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 20 Mar 2017 05:08:05 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 10 May 2017 11:48:04 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 16 May 2017 15:35:23 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Mon, 3 Jul 2017 11:46:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-04"}
